    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-20T03:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-20T03:25:00-05:00" n="591"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3205: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-20T11:00:00+02:35"
                            >December 20, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 21—6:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>244. Legation’s 243, December 19, 5 p.m. In making public the proposals and
                    Ethiopian reply, the Government issued following unofficial statement to correct
                    erroneous impression certain passages in proposals might create.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“One passage of the Franco-British proposals is susceptible of giving an
                        entirely false impression of the prior attitude of Ethiopia relative to the
                        plan of assistance of the League of Nations. The fourth paragraph of part II
                        of the proposals mentions the plan already prepared and accepted in
                        principle by the Emperor, and continues by declaring that Italy would take a
                        preponderant part in the services <pb facs="0822" n="720" xml:id="pg_720"/>
                        and that the principal adviser the plan might be an Italian. It should be
                        emphasized that at the time of the offer submitted to the tripartite
                        conference of Paris and also the subsequent acceptance in principle of the
                        plan of the Committee of Five, Ethiopia categorically rejected all Italian
                        personnel reserving its right of approval of every candidate to office of
                        employment under the plan.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Please see in this connection second paragraph of Legation’s 101, September 25, 9
                    p.m. [a.m.]<note n="27" xml:id="d591fn27">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_657">p. 657</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
